## 1. Product Requirements Document (PRD)

### 1.1 Vision
**Testify** is a self-hosted JEE/NEET test platform that runs on free tiers with a Next.js 16 frontend (Vercel) and an Express + ws backend (Railway/Render). It targets two audiences in one product:

- **Students** — take institute-scheduled timed papers (with JEE Advanced partial marking), practice papers, daily challenges, and review detailed analytics
- **Coaches/Admins** — manage a question bank, publish papers to batches, run analytics across students/papers/batches, manage credentials, merge duplicate topics

### 1.2 Core Features

| Feature | Notes |
|---|---|
| Cookie auth (students + admins) | Independent cookies, independent tables, dual-check on login |
| Multi-user isolation | Users only see their own sessions/results |
| Per-test leaderboards | Ranked by score, with attempt count |
| JEE Advanced partial marking | Subject to marking scheme; recomputed on question edit |
| Paper-level attempt limits | `attemptsAllowed` per set, per user |
| Unique paper names | DB-level uniqueness, no auto-deletion (papers persist forever) |
| Admin-managed question bank | `QuestionSet` + `Question` tables; admin has full editability |
| Question-delete reward | Student gets full marks for deleted questions (synthetic row in analytics) |
| Exam keyboard nav | Tab/Shift+Tab/arrows/Enter/Home/End, server-authoritative timer |
| Tests catalog | Tabs: Active → Institute available → Practice available → Attempted → Locked |
| Batch system | Students in multiple batches; papers in multiple batches; scheduled windows |
| Bulk-add roster | Paste email list → auto-create users with default password `"password123"` |
| Plain-text passwords | `UserCredential` table — explicit user request, no encryption |
| Manual topic clash detection | Sortable table, multi-select merge, recompute affected sessions synchronously |
| Student analytics | Weekly + by-subject + per-paper (real data) |
| Admin analytics | 4 views: overview, per-student, per-paper, per-batch |
| Late-start buffer | Per-BatchPaper grace period (default 10 min) for joining late; default 0-60 |
| No active tests card | Friendly empty state when nothing is live |

### 1.3 Non-functional
- $0/month — free tiers, self-hosted
- FE and BE deployable independently
- Express (not Fastify), plain `ws` (not socket.io)
- SQLite for now, Postgres deferred
- Local dev only for now
- TypeScript, App Router, Tailwind, KaTeX for LaTeX
- Light theme, generous padding, green + cyan accents
- Badge variants: `cyan | mint | forest | crimson | amber | muted`
- Heavy console logging (client + server)

### 1.4 Roles

**Student:**
- Take exams (institute / practice / daily challenge)
- See their analytics
- See leaderboards
- **Zero editability** on any content — always

**Admin:**
- Create/edit/delete question bank entries
- Create/edit papers (including marking scheme, time limit, attempts allowed, batch assignments, buffer minutes)
- Create/edit batches
- Add members (single + bulk) — auto-creates users with default password
- See all credentials in plain text; copy/export
- Manage topics (rename, promote orphan, merge with recompute)
- See all analytics (overview, students, papers, batches)
- **Full editability** on questions/marking even after attempts; on edit, **recompute every completed session's score synchronously**

### 1.5 Security & Auth Model
- Student cookie: `testify_session` (7-day)
- Admin cookie: `testify_admin` (7-day, separate)
- Admins in `data/admins.csv` (bcrypt)
- Admin tables: `Admin` + `AdminAuthSession` (independent of student tables)
- Login dual-check: `UserCredential.plainPassword === input` first, then `bcrypt.compare(input, User.passwordHash)`
- Audit-flagged issues that are **deferred**: unauthenticated `/api/admin/*` GETs, missing exam ownership checks, XSS sink in `MathRenderer`, TOCTOU in /exam/answer, daily challenge uniqueness, recompute-outside-transaction

### 1.6 Buffer / Grace Period (newest feature)
- **Semantics:** late-start shifts the exam window. Students can join anytime in `[scheduledStart, scheduledStart + bufferMinutes]`
- **Storage:** `BatchPaper.bufferMinutes Int @default(10)` (auto-applied to existing rows on db push)
- **Range:** 0-60 minutes (validated server-side, clamped client-side)
- **Scope:** per-BatchPaper (most flexible)
- **Once joined:** exam runs for `timeLimit` from `startTime` (no hard cap)
- **`scheduledEnd`** retained for display but no longer enforced
- **PRACTICE papers** skip the check entirely
- **Server-side errors:**
  - 423 (Locked) if `now < scheduledStart`: `{ error: "This exam isn't open yet. It opens at [time]." }`
  - 410 (Gone) if `now > scheduledStart + buffer`: `{ error: "You missed this exam's join window. The latest start was [time]." }`
  - 403 (Forbidden) if INSTITUTE paper but user in no assigned batch: `{ code: "NO_BATCH_ACCESS" }`
- **UI:**
  - Inline `Buffer (min)` number input next to datetime pickers in admin papers form
  - "Latest start: [time]" helper text + "Join window: [start → deadline]" in form
  - My Papers cards show "Buffer: X min" + new "Live/Past/Scheduled/Closed" status
  - Student `/tests` cards show "Join by: [deadline]" on INSTITUTE papers

