### 1.10 Conventions & Rules
- **No two papers may have the same name** — DB-level uniqueness
- **Every paper ever made stored in DB** — no auto-deletion
- **Each paper has `attemptsAllowed` setting** — per-user limit
- **Plain-text passwords OK in DB** (UserCredential table)
- **Auto-create new users when added by email** with default password `"password123"`
- **PRACTICE papers = batch-agnostic** (always visible to all logged-in users)
- **INSTITUTE papers require batch assignment** (enforced server-side)
- **"No active tests" = friendly info card** when `instituteFresh.length === 0`
- **In-progress exam per (user, set) blocks new starts with 409**
- **All admin analytics views** (overview, per-student, per-paper, per-batch)
- **Manual topic clash detection** — sortable table, multi-select merge
- **Recompute all affected sessions synchronously** when topics are merged
- **Prisma `/* */` block comments not supported** — use `//` style only
- **Heavy console logging** (client + server) — every fetch/click logged
- **User runs `npm`/`npx` commands manually** (Windows EPERM on `query_engine-windows.dll.node`)
- **Skip security audit work; focus on UX and MVP building**

### 1.11 Status Badge Variants
- `fresh=cyan/Available`
- `inProgress=mint/In Progress`
- `attempted=amber/Attempted`
- `exhausted=crimson/Locked`

### 1.12 Action Label Logic (student /tests cards)
- `fresh` → `Start`
- `inProgress` → `Resume`
- `attempted` → `Re-attempt (if attempts left) else View Result`
- `exhausted` → `Locked`

### 1.13 Resume / Start / View Result Flows
- **Resume:** click Resume → `router.push("/exam?sessionId=...inProgressSessionId")`
- **Start:** click Start → `POST /api/exam/start` with `{ setId }` → 200 `{ sessionId }` → push; 409 with `inProgressSessionId` → resume that; 423/410/403 → show error message
- **View result:** `router.push("/results/session/${set.lastSessionId}")`

### 1.14 Tests Catalog Section Order
1. Active (live right now)
2. Institute (available, scheduled in future)
3. Practice (available)
4. Attempted
5. Locked

### 1.15 Topbar
- **Student items:** Home, Tests, Results, Analysis
- **Admin pages via direct routes**, no admin nav in topbar (admin pages have their own sidebar via `(admin)/layout.tsx`)
- **Path detection:** `currentScreen = SCREENS.find(s => s.path === pathname)?.id || "dashboard"`
- **Dashboard layout `isFullBleed`:** `pathname === "/admin" || pathname === "/exam"`

### 1.16 Date/Time
- All timestamps stored as ISO 8601 UTC in DB
- Datetime pickers in form are local timezone
- Analytics uses IST (`istDateKey(d)` helper: `d.getTime() + IST offset`, then UTC date components)

### 1.17 Analytics Architecture
- **Student side:** computed client-side from `/api/student/history` + `/api/student/stats`
- **Admin side:** uses `buildSessionAnalytics` from `marking.ts` for per-session topic stats; aggregates computed in JS
- **Overview 30-day window:** pre-builds last 30 days in `dayMap`, only includes sessions within that range
- **Per-question difficulty:** sorts hardest-first by default; uses `session.analytics` JSON (`questions[]` with `status: "correct"|"skipped"|"wrong"`)
- **Topic breakdown** parses `session.analytics.topicAnalysis[]` aggregated across sessions

